%h2 Examples

%p There are several examples to help your experience with Netty. It is recommended to start from the first one and to finish to the last one.

%h3 Fundamental     

%ul
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/echo/package-summary.html">Echo</a> - the very basic client and server
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/discard/package-summary.html">Discard</a> - prevent OutOfMemoryError which is caused by writing too fast
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/uptime/package-summary.html">UpTime</a> - implement reliable client-side reconnection

%h3 Text protocols  

%ul
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/telnet/package-summary.html">Telnet</a> - a classic line-based network application
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/qotm/package-summary.html">Quote of the Moment</a> - broadcast UDP/IP client and server
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/securechat/package-summary.html">SecureChat</a> - an SSL-based chat server derived from the Telnet example

%h3 Binary protocols        

%ul
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/objectecho/package-summary.html">ObjectEcho</a> - exchange serializable Java objects
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/factorial/package-summary.html">Factorial</a> - write a stateful client / server based on custom binary protocol

%h3 HTTP    

%ul
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/http/snoop/package-summary.html">HTTP (Snoop)</a> - build your own extremely light-weight HTTP client and server
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/http/file/package-summary.html">HTTP (File Server)</a> - asynchronous large file streaming in HTTP
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/http/websocket/package-summary.html">Web Sockets</a> - add two-way full-duplex communication channels to HTTP using Web Sockets protocol

%h3 Cool stuff      

%ul
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/localtime/package-summary.html">LocalTime</a> - rapid protocol prototyping with Google Protocol Buffers integration

%h3 Advanced        

%ul
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/proxy/package-summary.html">Proxy Server</a> - write a highly efficient NIO proxy server
  %li <a href="#{site.stableReleaseVersion}/xref/org/jboss/netty/example/portunification/package-summary.html">Port Unification</a> - run heterogenous services listening on a single port

